<TITLE> Brazil closing in on Argentina's top ranking </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ZURICH, April 9 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Argentina remained top of the FIFA world rankings published on Wednesday but with just 10 points separating them from South American rivals Brazil. A 2-0 friendly win over Egypt last month helped Argentina hold top spot for the seventh consecutive month but Brazil narrowed the gap with a 1-0 victory in their friendly game against higher-ranked Sweden. There was no movement among the top seven sides but Greece secured their highest ranking, climbing above Portugal into eighth place after beating Luiz Felipe Scolari's men 2-1 last month. FIFA RANKINGS (previous positions in brackets): 1. (1) Argentina 2. (2) Brazil 3. (3) Italy 4. (4) Spain 5. (5) Germany 6. (6) Czech Republic 7. (7) France 8. (10) Greece 9. (8) Portugal 10. (9) Netherlands 11. (11) England 12. (13) Romania 13. (12) Croatia 14. (15) Ghana 15. (14) Scotland 16. (16) Mexico 17. (17) Cameroon 18. (19) Bulgaria 19. (20) Colombia 20. (22) Isra
